# Windows Development Environment Rules

This project is developed on Windows platform. Use PowerShell syntax for any system commands.

## Command Specifications:
- Use PowerShell syntax, not Linux/Unix commands
- Use backslash `\` or forward slash `/` as path separator (PowerShell compatible)
- Avoid using `&&` connector, use semicolon `;` or execute separately
- Use PowerShell cmdlets for file operations (e.g., `Get-ChildItem`, `Copy-Item`)

## Common Command Mapping:
- `ls` → `Get-ChildItem` or `dir`
- `cat` → `Get-Content`
- `cp` → `Copy-Item`
- `mv` → `Move-Item`
- `rm` → `Remove-Item`